This paper deals with image interpolation and morphing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves enforcing an image prior, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular deep learning technique used in computer vision and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves optimization and constraint satisfaction, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
